                    </div>
                    <span>the other reviews you'll read have more them amply discussed the actors, the music and such so I just wish to comment on what Otto Preminger brings to a film.  
<br />
<br />Two scenes come to mind in this film.  Both long shots.  Actor in the background, alone.  The camera slowly pans down and there we see (gasp!)  the top of a chair! or, in the second scene, we find a vase full of flowers in the foreground.  Neither of these two items would get even a snicker in today's blood thirsty movie audiences but in the hands of a master, they are terrifying.
<br />
<br />A classic of mood, shadow and tension.  This is a movie of studied suspense.  Should be required for all film students.
<br />
<br />You're going to love this one!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Dana Andrews!!!!!!</div>
